%% Diagram: Burn-after-read with row lock
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant API as Read service
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant S3 as Object storage

    C->>API: GET /aB3kF9x
    API->>DB: BEGIN
    API->>DB: SELECT row FOR UPDATE
    DB-->>API: burn_after_read=true, deleted_at=null
    API->>DB: UPDATE read_count=1, deleted_at=NOW()
    API->>S3: GET /pastes/aB3kF9x.zst
    S3-->>API: compressed content
    API->>DB: COMMIT
    API->>S3: DELETE /pastes/aB3kF9x.zst (async)
    API-->>C: 200 {content} (Cache-Control: no-store)
    Note over API,DB: Concurrent readers see deleted_at != null<br/>and receive 410 Gone
